mahla zamani is an iranian fashion designer, journalist and expert on iranian traditional clothing. she established the first fashion exhibition after the iranian revolution (1979) and put significant effort in popularizing iranian stylish clothing. in her view, iranians need to revive their past and dress in elegant colorful and traditional styles (instead of black and arabian dresses). her efforts in advertising persian, qashqai, kurdish, turkmen and baloch dress styles attracted international attention. she has been attacked by fundamentalist circles and newspapers repeatedly.